From ed5cb05716146787d16b497f527477330d84b31f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 08:36:54 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] third_party/hal_sifli: don't error on maybe-uninitialized

GCC 13 flags bt_rf_fulcal.c in the SiFli vendor SDK with
-Werror=maybe-uninitialized, breaking the build on toolchains other
than the bundled ARM GNU 14. Demote it to a warning for the vendor
library only.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_0193EzyJ5pjQDBAgPjUoy4xn
Signed-off-by: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 third_party/hal_sifli/wscript_build | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/third_party/hal_sifli/wscript_build b/third_party/hal_sifli/wscript_build
index 42a2dc97..3c99b231 100644
--- a/third_party/hal_sifli/wscript_build
+++ b/third_party/hal_sifli/wscript_build
@@ -208,5 +208,6 @@ bld.stlib(
         '-Wno-unused-but-set-variable',
         '-Wno-sign-compare',
         '-Wno-type-limits',
+        '-Wno-error=maybe-uninitialized',
     ],
 )
-- 
2.43.0

